verbose_text: These findings provide unique insight into the role of insulin signaling in mediating retinal effects in diabetes, and open new avenues for treating the retinal complications of diabetes mellitus [XREF_BIBR]., An in vitro study showed that PLGF-1 induced a reversible decrease in transepithelial resistance and enhanced tritiated insulin flux.
